    <questiontext format="markdown">
      <text><![CDATA[**33.1 E1 1D Boundary Value Problem**

<p>
  Let \( y = y(x) \) be a solution to the boundary value problem
</p>
<p>
  \(\displaystyle {@p*'diff(y,x,2) + q*'diff(y,x) + r*y(x) = s@} \quad 0 < x < {@L@} \)
</p>
<p>
  \( y(0) = {@y0@} \), \( y(0.75) = {@y3@} \)
</p>
<p>
  Using a mesh width of \( h = {@h@} \) obtain a central difference approximation to the differential
  equation and hence find \( y_1 \approx y({@h@}) \) and \( y_2 \approx y({@2*h@}) \).
</p>

\\\(y_1=\\\) [[input:S_u1]] [[validation:S_u1]] [[feedback:u1]]

\\\(y_2=\\\) [[input:S_u2]] [[validation:S_u2]] [[feedback:u2]]]]></text>
    </questiontext>
